    <caseIntroduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Ghana loses around 2% of its forest cover per year through deforestation, with forest degradation presenting an even bigger problem. Agricultural expansion, wood harvesting, development, and (illegal) mining are all driving factors. </p>
<p>Ghana has a highly agrarian economy which both drives degradation and is threatened by the ecological impacts of forest degradation and loss.</p>
<p>Agriculture is the second largest source of emissions in Ghana (38%), and the sector with the fastest growth rate since 1990.</p>
<p>Cocoa production accounts for about 16% of total GDP. Climate change is likely to shift the temporal zone in which cocoa can be produced, with production also affected by reduced precipitation and higher annual temperatures.</p>]]></Value>
    </caseIntroduction>
